Colleague,
 
I write to congratulate you on your retirement from the Public Service. I would like to take this opportunity to thank you for your contribution to the Public Service of Canada and wish you well as you move on to new challenges. I also wish to remind you that it is important to ensure that you avoid any conflict of interest between your current and your future responsibilities if you are considering making a transition to employment outside of the public service.
 
As you are in a designated position, you are obliged to observe the post-employment compliance measures set out in section 4 (e) of the <a href="http://iservice.prv/eng/is/ve/code_of_conduct/index.shtml">ESDC Code of Conduct</a> (the Code). Compliance with the post-employment provisions is intended to protect both you and the Government from allegations concerning preferential treatment, privileged access to government officials or use of government information not generally available to the public.
 
Furthermore, as stipulated in <a href="http://iservice.prv/eng/is/ve/code_of_conduct/index.shtml">the Code</a>, there is a limitation period of one year, which will commence on the date of your departure. Before your departure and during this one-year limitation period, you are required to submit a <a href="http://hrsc-csrh.prv/Request/New/COI?FormTypeInd=0">Conflict of Interest Disclosure</a> to the <a href="mailto:NC-OVE-AC-BVE@hrsdc-rhdcc.gc.ca">Office of Values and Ethics</a> all firm offers and acceptance of employment or activities outside the federal government. This includes but is not limited to offers from entities with which you had significant official dealings personally, or through your subordinates, during your last year of service.

Additionally, during the one year period you should not:
 
a) accept appointment to a board of directors of, or employment with, private entities with which you had significant official dealings directly, or through your subordinates, during the year immediately preceding your departure;
 
b) make representations to any government organization on behalf of persons or entities outside of the public service with which you or your subordinates have had significant official dealings during the one year immediately prior to the termination of your service; or
 
c) give advice to your clients or employer using information that is not publicly available concerning the programs or policies of the Department or concerning the programs or policies of the departments or organizations with which you had a direct and substantial relationship.
 
This limitation period may, however be waived or reduced after consideration of various factors, as specified in the Code, in regards to both your situation and the public interest. If you wish to make a request to waive or reduce the limitation period, please contact the Office of Values and Ethics through ESDC?s <a href="http://hrsc-csrh.prv/Webforms/NewRequest.aspx?RequestType=HRSC&amp;FormTypeInd=0">Human Resources Service Centre</a>.
 
You will be advised in writing of any decision in relation to your specific situation.
 
Furthermore, as a designated public office holder, the Lobbying Act prohibits you, for a period of five years, from:

a) working as a consultant lobbyist,
b) carrying out lobbying activities on behalf of an organization,
c) working for a corporation if lobbying constitutes a significant part (20% or more) of your work.
 
The Commissioner of Lobbying is empowered to grant exemptions to the five-year prohibition on lobbying in certain situations described in the Lobbying Act. Please consult the <a href="https://lobbycanada.gc.ca/en/">Office of the Commissioner of Lobbying of Canada</a> website for more detailed information.
 
Officers at the Office of Values and Ethics would be pleased to explain the post-employment provisions further and answer any questions you may have. Should you require additional information, please do not hesitate to contact the Office of Values and Ethics through the ESDC?s <a href="http://hrsc-csrh.prv/Webforms/NewRequest.aspx?RequestType=HRSC&amp;FormTypeInd=0">Human Resources Service Centre</a> or by email at <a href="mailto:NC-OVE-AC-BVE@hrsdc-rhdcc.gc.ca">NC-OVE-AC-BVE@hrsdc-rhdcc.gc.ca</a> 

Yours sincerely,
 
 
Darl?ne de Gravina
Assistant Deputy Minister
Human Resources Services Branch','2015-03-30T00:00:00',NULL,N'Robichaud, Yves [NC]',N'Leblanc, Chantal x [NC]','2015-03-30T07:42:48.493','2021-05-11T13:42:48.793',34)
